Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Cover and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}. Cut into thirds. Drain the @King Prawns{225%g}.

Once hot, fry the prawns and green beans, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Once the prawns have browned, stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}.

Add the @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water{100%ml}.

> See pantry for sugar and water.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}.

Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down slightly. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.

Next, stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g}.

Bring to the boil, then stir in the @Butter{20%g}. Remove from the heat.

> See pantry for butter.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

Serve your curry and rice in #bowls{}.

Enjoy!